var s1 = new cc.Sprite('res/hero.png');
batch.addChild(s1);
this.addChild(batch);
```

output:
The sprite `s1` uses a different texture (`res/hero.png`) than the batch node (`res/atlas.png`). SpriteBatchNode requires all child sprites to use the same texture. Fix: load the sprite from the same texture or a frame within the atlas:
```js
var batch = new cc.SpriteBatchNode('res/atlas.png');
var s1 = new cc.Sprite('res/atlas.png'); // same texture
batch.addChild(s1);
this.addChild(batch);
```

